I"w<p>The <code>linky</code> sensor platform is retrieving the consumption of your home from the <a href="https://www.enedis.fr/linky-compteur-communicant">Linky electric meter</a>.</p>
<h2>Setup the integration</h2>
<p>You need to create an Enedis account <a href="https://espace-client-connexion.enedis.fr/auth/UI/Login?realm=particuliers">here</a> if you don’t have one already.</p>
<h3>Via the frontend</h3>
<p>Menu: <em>Configuration</em> -&gt; <em>Integrations</em></p>
<p>Search for “Linky”, add your credentials, click submit, you are done !</p>
<h3>Via the configuration file</h3>
<p>Add the Linky sensor to your <code>configuration.yaml</code> file like below:</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml"># Example configuration.yaml entry
linky:
  - username: YOUR_LINKY_USERNAME
    password: YOUR_LINKY_PASSWORD
</code></pre>
<div class="config-vars">
  <h3><a class="title-link" name="configuration-variables" href="#configuration-variables"></a> Configuration Variables</h3>
  <dl class=''><dt><a class='title-link' name='username' href='#username'></a> username</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>The Enedis account username.</p>
</span></p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='password' href='#password'></a> password</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Required)</span><span class='description'><p>The Enedis account password.</p>
</span></p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='timeout' href='#timeout'></a> timeout</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='integer'>integer</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>Timeout to wait for the Enedis API connection.</p>
</span></p><p class='default'>
Default value: <p>10</p>
</p></dd></dl>
</div>
